Package org.ejbca.ui.cli.ca

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BaseCaAdminCommand
    Base for CA commands, contains common functions for CA operations
    CaActivateCACommand
    Activates the specified HSM CA.
    CaChangeCATokenSignAlgCommand
    Changes the signature algorithm and possible keyspec of a CA token.
    CaChangeCertProfileCommand
    Changes the certificate profile of a CA.
    CaChangeCryptoTokenCommand
    CLI command to change crypto token and CA token properties of a CA.
    CaCreateCrlCommand
    Issues a new CRL from the CA.
    CaDeactivateCACommand
    Makes the specified HSM CA offline.
    CaEditCaCommand
    Changes fields in a CA.
    CaEditCertificateProfileCommand
    Changes fields in a Certificate Profile.
    CaEditPublisherCommand
    Changes fields in a Publisher.
    CaExportCACommand
    Exports CA as a PKCS#12 or PKCS#8 file
    CaExportProfilesCommand
    Export profiles from the database to XML-files.
    CaGetCrlCommand
    Retrieves the latest CRL from a CA.
    CaGetCrlInfo
    List information about the latest CRL from each CA.
    CaGetFieldValueCommand
    Changes fields in a CA.
    CaImportCACertCommand
    Imports a PEM file and creates a new external CA representation from it.
    CaImportCACommand
    Imports a keystore and creates a new X509 CA from it
    CaImportCertCommand
    Imports a certificate file to the database.
    CaImportCertDirCommand
    Imports certificate files to the database for a given CA
    CaImportCRLCommand
    Imports a CRL file to the database.
    CaImportProfilesCommand
    Import profiles from XML-files to the database.
    CaInfoCommand
    Shows info about a CA.
    CaInitCommand  
    CaListCAsCommand
    Lists the names of all available CAs.
    CaListExpiredCommand
    List certificates that will expire within the given number of days.
    CaListFieldsCommand
    Lists the fields of a CA.
    CaListPublishersCommand
    List Publishers in the system.
    CaMergeCryptoTokenCommand
    CLI command to consolidate the referenced PKCS#11 Crypto Tokens.
    CaRemoveKeyStoreCommand
    Remove the CA token keystore from a CA.
    CaRemovePublisherCommand
    Remove a Publisher from the system.
    CaRenewCACommand
    Renews the CA certificate and optionally regenerates the key pair.
    CARepublishCommand
    Re-publishes the certificates of all users belonging to a particular CA.
    CaRestoreKeyStoreCommand
    Restore a CA token keystore from a PKCS12 file.
    GetCaCertCommand
    Export any CA certificate.
    ImportMSCACertificates
    Used for importing certificates from a MS CA dump.
    UpdatePublicKeyBlacklistCommand
    Imports certificate files to the database for a given CA
